            "title": "Gold miner Newmont beats quarterly profit estimates on bullion rally",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>(Reuters) -Newmont surpassed Wall Street expectations for third-quarter profit on Thursday, as the world's top gold miner benefited from a rally in bullion prices.</p><p>\n              Bullion prices, notoriously sensitive to uncertainty, have been on the rise over the past few quarters. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n              Spot gold prices have consistently touched record highs as uncertainty over U.S. President Donald Trump's tariff plans and geopolitical concerns raised the precious metal's safe-haven appeal.</p><p>\n              Gold prices averaged at $3,574.95 per ounce in the three months ended September 30, more than 43% above levels seen a year earlier.</p><p>\n              Newmont's quarterly gold output fell to 1.42 million ounces, compared with 1.67 million ounces a year ago. </p><p>\n              The average realized price for gold was $3,539 per ounce in the third quarter, compared with $2,518 per ounce a year earlier.</p><p>\n              The gold miner posted quarterly profit of $1.71 per share on an adjusted basis, beating analysts' average estimate of $1.43, according to data compiled by LSEG.</p><p>\n               (Reporting by Sumit Saha in Bengaluru; Editing by Shreya Biswas)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/gold-miner-newmont-beats-quarterly-profit-estimates-on-bullion-rally-ce7d5dd8d18bf020",
            "pub_date": "2025-10-24 04:20:46",
            "source": "marketscreener",
